The paper deals with the problem of linear separability of stochastic geometric objects, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves algorithms and complexity analysis, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also discusses the expected separation-margin, which is a measure of the quality of the separation, indicating that it could belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.LG (Machine Learning).
